<cell id="cell-0"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type># LLM Fundamentals

Hands-on exploration of tokenization, context windows, and generation parameters.</cell id="cell-0">
<cell id="cell-1"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>## 1. Tokenization — Seeing Text as a Model Does</cell id="cell-1">
<cell id="cell-2"># Install: pip install tiktoken
import tiktoken

encoder = tiktoken.get_encoding("cl100k_base")  # Used by GPT-4

texts = [
    "Hello world",
    "AI architect",
    "Retrieval-Augmented Generation",
    "supercalifragilistic",
    "The capital of France is Paris.",
]

for text in texts:
    tokens = encoder.encode(text)
    print(f"Text: {text!r}")
    print(f"  Tokens: {tokens}")
    print(f"  Count: {len(tokens)}")
    print(f"  Decoded: {[encoder.decode([t]) for t in tokens]}")
    print()</cell id="cell-2">
<cell id="cell-3"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>## 2. Token Cost Estimator

Pricing is per token. Let's build a simple cost estimator.</cell id="cell-3">
<cell id="cell-4">def estimate_cost(text: str, model: str = "gpt-4o") -> dict:
    """Estimate the token count and cost for a given text."""
    encoder = tiktoken.get_encoding("cl100k_base")
    token_count = len(encoder.encode(text))

    # Approximate prices per 1M tokens (input) as of early 2025
    prices_per_1m = {
        "gpt-4o": 2.50,
        "gpt-4o-mini": 0.15,
        "claude-3-5-sonnet": 3.00,
        "claude-3-haiku": 0.25,
    }

    price = prices_per_1m.get(model, 3.00)
    cost = (token_count / 1_000_000) * price

    return {
        "model": model,
        "token_count": token_count,
        "cost_usd": round(cost, 6),
        "chars_per_token": round(len(text) / token_count, 2),
    }

long_text = "AI architects design systems that integrate machine learning models into production environments. " * 100

for model in ["gpt-4o", "gpt-4o-mini", "claude-3-5-sonnet", "claude-3-haiku"]:
    result = estimate_cost(long_text, model)
    print(f"{result['model']}: {result['token_count']} tokens → ${result['cost_usd']:.4f}")</cell id="cell-4">
<cell id="cell-5"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>## 3. Context Window Simulation

Demonstrating what happens when input exceeds the context window.</cell id="cell-5">
<cell id="cell-6">def check_context_fit(text: str, context_window: int = 128_000) -> dict:
    """Check if text fits in a model's context window."""
    encoder = tiktoken.get_encoding("cl100k_base")
    token_count = len(encoder.encode(text))
    fits = token_count <= context_window
    overflow = max(0, token_count - context_window)

    return {
        "token_count": token_count,
        "context_window": context_window,
        "fits": fits,
        "overflow_tokens": overflow,
        "utilization_pct": round(token_count / context_window * 100, 1),
    }

# Simulate a long document
document = "This is a research paper paragraph about machine learning. " * 500
result = check_context_fit(document, context_window=8192)  # Older model limit

print(f"Document: {result['token_count']} tokens")
print(f"Context window: {result['context_window']}")
print(f"Fits: {result['fits']}")
print(f"Overflow: {result['overflow_tokens']} tokens")
print(f"Utilization: {result['utilization_pct']}%")</cell id="cell-6">
<cell id="cell-7"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>## 4. Temperature Effect Simulation

Temperature controls the randomness of token selection. Let's simulate probability distributions.</cell id="cell-7">
<cell id="cell-8">import math
import random

def softmax_with_temperature(logits: list[float], temperature: float) -> list[float]:
    """Apply temperature scaling to logits and compute softmax."""
    if temperature == 0:
        # Greedy: pick the max
        max_idx = logits.index(max(logits))
        return [1.0 if i == max_idx else 0.0 for i in range(len(logits))]

    scaled = [l / temperature for l in logits]
    exp_vals = [math.exp(v - max(scaled)) for v in scaled]  # Numerically stable
    total = sum(exp_vals)
    return [v / total for v in exp_vals]

# Simulated logits for next token candidates
vocab = ["Paris", "Lyon", "Marseille", "Berlin", "London"]
raw_logits = [5.2, 2.1, 1.8, 0.5, 0.3]

print("Effect of Temperature on Token Probabilities")
print("=" * 55)
print(f"{'Token':<12}", end="")
for temp in [0.0, 0.3, 0.7, 1.0, 2.0]:
    print(f"  T={temp}", end="")
print()
print("-" * 55)

for i, token in enumerate(vocab):
    print(f"{token:<12}", end="")
    for temp in [0.0, 0.3, 0.7, 1.0, 2.0]:
        probs = softmax_with_temperature(raw_logits, temp)
        print(f"  {probs[i]:.3f}", end="")
    print()</cell id="cell-8">
